Minkowski region 

In general, the propagators are tempered distributions in the Minkowski region .  However, if distribution-type singularities are present only below a finite momentum value , the propagators may be treated as ordinary functions for .  
In this case, therefore, the asymptotic formulas derived above  are also applied to the large Minkowski momenta with .

If the distribution-type singularities occur for arbitrarily large momenta, the asymptotic behavior of the propagators should be studied in terms of the average values which are obtained by smearing with suitable test functions.  
It is shown that the averaged gluon propagator in the Minkowski region has again the same asymptotic form as given above, independent of the chosen test function. 

