The Landau gauge is indeed a fixed point, but it is an IR fixed point.  
Hence, the superconvergence at the Landau gauge is UV unstable.
If the theory starts at a non-zero , then the superconvergence relation can not be maintained no matter how small the running gauge parameter  at  may be. 
